explanation: The solution iterates over the range [l, r] and checks each number to see if its digits are in non-decreasing order. It uses a flag to track whether the digits are non-decreasing, and if they are, it increments the result. The result is taken modulo 10^9 + 7 to avoid overflow. The time complexity is O((r-l+1) * log(r)) because converting a string to an integer takes O(log(r)) time, and there are (r-l+1) numbers in the range.

